        "content": "Recently Bernie Sanders put it in a different form. He tweeted out, “If we are a nation that can pay baseball players hundreds of millions of dollars, don’t tell me we can’t afford to pay teachers the salaries they deserve.”10 There is some typical Sanders obfuscation here. “We” don’t pay baseball players hundreds of millions; the owners of the teams do. The taxpayer doesn’t bankroll baseball salaries the way he bankrolls teacher salaries.",
