        "page": 108,
        "location": "1951-1954",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Sunday, February 7, 2021 1:28:00 PM",
        "content": "This is presumably also why in the immediate wake of great disasters—a flood, a blackout, or an economic collapse—people tend to behave the same way, reverting to a rough-and-ready communism. However briefly, hierarchies and markets and the like become luxuries that no one can afford. Anyone who has lived through such a moment can speak to their peculiar qualities, the way that strangers become sisters and brothers and human society itself seems to be reborn.",
