        "page": 108,
        "location": "1955-1957",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Sunday, February 7, 2021 1:29:43 PM",
        "content": "In fact, communism is the foundation of all human sociability. It is what makes society possible. There is always an assumption that anyone who is not an enemy can be expected to act on the principle of “from each according to their abilities,” at least to an extent: for example, if one needs to figure out how to get somewhere and the other knows the way.",
