        "page": 166,
        "location": "2977-2980",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Thursday, February 11, 2021 8:56:53 PM",
        "content": "We have perhaps a general principle: to make something saleable, in a human economy, one needs to first rip it from its context. That’s what slaves are: people stolen from the community that made them what they are. As strangers to their new communities, slaves no longer had mothers, fathers, kin of any sort. This is why they could be bought and sold or even killed: because the only relation they had was to their owners.",
