        "page": 414,
        "location": "7451-7454",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Monday, February 22, 2021 12:38:22 PM",
        "content": "I have already pointed out that modern money is based on government debt, and that governments borrow money in order to finance wars. This is just as true today as it was in the age of King Phillip II. The creation of central banks represented a permanent institutionalization of that marriage between the interests of warriors and financiers that had already begun to emerge in Renaissance Italy and that eventually became the foundation of financial capitalism.",
