        "page": 79,
        "location": "1209-1212",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, June 5, 2021 2:35:35 PM",
        "content": "Yet this absurd line of argument is in essence how free-trade economists justify rapid, large-scale trade liberalization in developing countries. They claim that developing country producers need to be exposed to as much competition as possible right now, so that they have the incentive to raise their productivity in order to survive. Protection, by contrast, only creates complacency and sloth. The earlier the exposure, the argument goes, the better it is for economic development.",
