        "location": "2235-2238",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Wednesday, June 9, 2021 10:50:26 PM",
        "content": "‘Patents are only one means for promoting discovery and invention. Scientific curiosity, coupled with the desire to benefit humanity, has been of far greater importance throughout history.’5 Countless researchers all over the world come up with new ideas all the time, even when they do not directly profit from them.",
