        "page": 167,
        "location": "2550-2552",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Thursday, June 10, 2021 9:33:56 PM",
        "content": "This is why, historically, countries did not protect foreigners’ intellectual property very well (or at all) when they needed to import knowledge. If knowledge is like water that flows downhill, then today’s IPR system is like a dam that turns potentially fertile fields into a technological dustbowl. This situation clearly needs fixing.",
