        "page": 229,
        "location": "3508-3512",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, June 12, 2021 4:57:33 PM",
        "content": "‘Living for today’ or being ‘easy-going’ – words that many people associate with Africa and Latin America nowadays – are also the consequences of economic conditions. In a slowly changing economy, there is not much need to plan for the future; people plan for the future only when they anticipate new opportunities (e.g., new careers) or unexpected shocks (e.g., a sudden inflow of new imports). Moreover, poor economies offer few devices with which people can plan for the future (e.g., credit, insurance, contracts).",
