        "content": "I think that reversal of feeling is common. Writers certainly experience it, or at least I personally find it hard even to look at something I have written at the point when it is printed. All I want to do is think about the next piece or book. Jazz musicians have told me that they hate listening to recordings immediately after they have made them. Then, they can hear nothing but mistakes: a few years later, they may sound fine.",
