        "content": "Our mental gaze-radar detects it quickly, and even if we are utterly safe, we feel a quiver of warning inside. The omen is visceral, deep, oddly maddening. And it’s not just psychological. Being stared at increases arousal, raising the heartbeat and altering the galvanic skin response, especially if the victim cannot counter or escape.’ In pubs, staring can be a provocation to fight.",
