        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Monday, June 21, 2021 9:24:30 PM",
        "content": "In psychological tests, people of all nationalities, genders and ethnic groups, it seems, declare the same photographed faces to be attractive. But such objectivity diminishes sharply in experiments in which the actual people are introduced to each other. The more time they spend together, the less objective agreement there is. In practice, attractiveness depends to a surprising extent on the individuality of the people involved. Of those married to identical twins, only 10 per cent declared that they might have fallen for the other – almost visually indiscernible – twin.",
