        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Monday, September 27, 2021 3:02:53 PM",
        "content": "“I’m more likely to try a new restaurant when I move to a city than when I’m leaving it,” explains data scientist and blogger Chris Stucchio, a veteran of grappling with the explore/exploit tradeoff in both his work and his life. “I mostly go to restaurants I know and love now, because I know I’m going to be leaving New York fairly soon. Whereas a couple years ago I moved to Pune, India, and I just would eat friggin’ everywhere that didn’t look like it was gonna kill me. And as I was leaving the city I went back to all my old favorites, rather than trying out new stuff.… Even if I find a slightly better place, I’m only going to go there once or twice, so why take the risk?”",
