        "content": "Research in machine learning has yielded several concrete strategies for detecting overfitting, and one of the most important is what’s known as Cross-Validation. Simply put, Cross-Validation means assessing not only how well a model fits the data it’s given, but how well it generalizes to data it hasn’t seen. Paradoxically, this may involve using less data.",
