        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Thursday, September 30, 2021 9:40:30 PM",
        "content": "It was something else, too: a powerful computational technique called Lagrangian Relaxation. The idea behind Lagrangian Relaxation is simple. An optimization problem has two parts: the rules and the scorekeeping. In Lagrangian Relaxation, we take some of the problem’s constraints and bake them into the scoring system instead. That is, we take the impossible and downgrade it to costly.",
