        "page": 272,
        "location": "4162-4164",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, October 2, 2021 9:07:12 PM",
        "content": "Optimal stopping problems spring from the irreversibility and irrevocability of time; the explore/exploit dilemma, from time’s limited supply. Relaxation and randomization emerge as vital and necessary strategies for dealing with the ineluctable complexity of challenges like trip planning and vaccinations.",
