        "bookTile": "Algorithms to Live By",
        "page": 277,
        "location": "4241-4242",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, October 2, 2021 9:40:06 PM",
        "content": "In rock-paper-scissors, scrutinizing your opponent’s face for signs of what they might throw next may not be worthwhile, if you know that simply throwing at random is an unbeatable strategy in the long run.",
        "type": "HIGHLIGHT"
