        "bookTile": "Superforecasting",
        "page": 18,
        "location": "269-273",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Tuesday, October 5, 2021 5:09:14 PM",
        "content": "Which means no revision. And without revision, there can be no improvement. Imagine a world in which people love to run, but they have no idea how fast the average person runs, or how fast the best could run, because runners have never agreed to basic ground rules—stay on the track, begin the race when the gun is fired, end it after a specified distance—and there are no independent race officials and timekeepers measuring results. How likely is it that running times are improving in this world? Not very. Are the best runners running as fast as human beings are physically capable? Again, probably not.",
