        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Thursday, October 7, 2021 9:41:27 PM",
        "content": "If it’s true that probabilistic thinking is essential to accurate forecasting, and it-was-meant-to-happen thinking undermines probabilistic thinking, we should expect superforecasters to be much less inclined to see things as fated.",
