        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, October 23, 2021 10:17:40 AM",
        "content": "Each time they celebrated a flight that made it into orbit, they were encouraging their engineers to focus on the fact that the launch resulted in a success rather than on the faulty processes that could jeopardize future launches. That left NASA rewarding luck and repeating problematic practices, failing to rethink what qualified as an acceptable risk.",
