        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, November 20, 2021 11:02:20 AM",
        "content": "We understand, for instance, that a salary alone will not motivate people to risk their lives. Police officers, firefighters, soldiers—they don’t die for their weekly pay. It’s the social norms—pride in their profession and a sense of duty—that will motivate them to give up their lives and health.",
