        "content": "Even a scientific paper begins with an abstract that serves a similar purpose to a newspaper headline: it tells you what happened and what it means. A good journalist doesn’t begin reporting with the conclusion in mind; a good scientist doesn’t decide on the results before the experiment has been run. (I can’t vouch for what a good management consultant does.) But once both journalists and scientists have discovered something of interest, they want to give their audiences some pointers as to what it is. The same is true for chart designers.",
