        "content": "The Dollar Auction’s significant characteristic is that it is based on the problem of how to deal with “sunk costs.” A sunk cost is an investment that cannot be retrieved. In this game it is the money one has already bid if he or she is one of the final two bidders. One will either spend that money buying the dollar by being the highest bidder in the auction, or paying for nothing by staying in and finishing second.",
        "type": "HIGHLIGHT"
