        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Thursday, April 14, 2022 8:05:12 PM",
        "content": "Whether it is competitors conducting business, couples negotiating understandings, or anxious citizens vying for flu vaccines, situations can often be illustrated as prisoner’s dilemmas. The parties involved will often be better off collectively if each resists the temptation to go it alone and instead trusts or cooperates with the other person. Both parties’ pursuing their own interests often leads to a worse outcome than do loyalty and cooperation.",
