        "content": "Many economists, ourselves included, tout the advantages of the free market. The theory behind this conclusion relies on a price system that guides individual behavior. In most strategic interactions, there is no invisible hand of prices to guide the baker or the butcher or anyone else. Thus there is no reason to expect that the outcome of a game will be good for the players or society. It may not be enough to play a game well—you must also be sure you are playing the right game.",
