        "content": "The United States wanted democratic nations and political stability for the world, for reasons of moral righteousness, peace, and economic gain. There was a quest for balance of power. The Soviets wanted instability, an imbalance of power, for reasons of survival. For the Soviets, strong nations were threats, while weak nations were not. This disparity would form the fabric of the Iron Curtain.",
