        "page": 375,
        "location": "5741-5744",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Tuesday, January 31, 2023 12:36:26 PM",
        "content": "A people rapidly increases its population when all the younger members of a family are in a position to set up establishments. The peasant needs a numerous labor force, and it is obviously to his interest to be able to employ his children until the age when they become adult. If the latter can set up establishments in their turn, they don’t remain a charge on their father—but it’s quite different when the father is obliged to feed them from his own land, and for all their lives. In that case, of course, the birthrate falls.",
