        "authors": "Adolf Hitler",
        "bookTile": "Hitler's Table Talk 1941-1944: Secret Conversations",
        "page": 517,
        "location": "7920-7925",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Sunday, February 19, 2023 10:35:19 PM",
        "content": "This implies both privileges and obligations, the obligation of submitting to a most rigorous upbringing and the privilege of the healthy enjoyment of life. If a German soldier is expected to be ready to sacrifice his life without demur, then he is entitled to love freely and without restriction. In life, battle and love go hand in hand, and the inhibited little bourgeois must be content with the crumbs which remain. But if the warrior is to be kept in fighting trim, he must not be pestered with religious precepts which ordain abstinence of the flesh. A healthy-minded man simply smiles when a saint of the Catholic Church like St. Anthony bids him eschew the greatest joy that life has to give, and offers him the solace of self-mortification and castigation in its place.",
