        "page": 593,
        "location": "9085-9089",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, February 25, 2023 8:55:26 PM",
        "content": "Speaking generally, it would be unjust to reproach an artist—be he sculptor or singer—because his talents fade with age. Rather than emphasize the many faults that are to be found in the later works of Lovis Corinth, we should remember with delight the truly magnificent youth pictures of his earlier days. It should be the task of any reasonable culture policy to discover talent early, to encourage and foster it, and so give it the opportunity of reaching its highest fruition for the benefit of both the present and posterity.",
