        "page": 602,
        "location": "9229-9233",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, February 25, 2023 10:03:06 PM",
        "content": "The activities of the Church in Spain are no different from those of the Catholic Church in our own country, or indeed from those of most Churches in any other country. Any Church, provided it is in a position to exert influence on the civil régime, will, as a matter of principle, support or tolerate only such a régime as knows and recognizes no form of popular organization other than one under the aegis of the Church, and is therefore dependent, for purposes of general administration, solely on the Church, as the only organized leadership of the people.",
