        "page": 633,
        "location": "9706-9709",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Monday, February 27, 2023 4:29:47 PM",
        "content": "In Japan the principle of corporate family responsibility is so deeply rooted, that every family exercising influence, whether in the Army or in the political field, considers it a duty, as a matter of course, to prevent any member from doing anything contrary to the national interest. If their efforts are not successful and they feel that the national reputation of the family has been smirched by the erring son, then all the male members commit hari-kiri, to clear the family honor.",
