        "location": "8094-8097",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, April 8, 2023 2:39:42 PM",
        "content": "Combinations of the two occur frequently; even genuine friendship is always a mixture of selfishness and sympathy. Selfishness lies in the pleasure in the presence of the friend, whose individuality corresponds to our own, and it almost invariably constitutes the greatest part; sympathy shows itself in a sincere participation in the friend’s weal and woe, and in the disinterested sacrifices made for the latter.",
