        "bookTile": "Twilight of Idols and Anti-Christ",
        "page": 91,
        "location": "1394-1399",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Tuesday, May 30, 2023 9:10:42 PM",
        "content": "The most powerful men have always inspired the architects; the architect has always been influenced by power. Pride, victory over weight and gravity, the will to power, seek to render themselves visible in a building; architecture is a kind of rhetoric of power, now persuasive, even cajoling in form, now bluntly imperious. The highest feeling of power and security finds expression in that which possesses grand style. Power which no longer requires proving; which disdains to please; which is slow to answer; which is conscious of no witness around it; which lives oblivious of the existence of any opposition; which reposes in itself, fatalistic, a law among laws: that is what speaks of itself in the form of grand style.",
