        "bookTile": "The Gay Science",
        "page": 203,
        "location": "3345-3348",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Friday, June 9, 2023 1:05:45 PM",
        "content": "When it rains.— It is raining, and I think of the poor who now huddle together with their many cares and without any practice at concealing these: each is ready and willing to hurt the other and to create for himself a wretched kind of pleasure even when the weather is bad. That and only that is the poverty of the poor.",
