        "content": "You superior humans, the worst about you is: that none of you has learned to dance as one has to dance– dance away beyond yourselves! What does it matter that you have failed! How much is yet possible! So just learn to laugh away beyond yourselves! Lift up your hearts, you fine dancers, high! higher! And do not forget to laugh well too! This laugher’s crown, this rose-wreath crown: to you, my brothers, I throw this crown! Laughter I have pronounced holy; you superior humans, learn from me– to laugh!",
