        "content": "‘For fear– that is the feeling which is inherited and fundamental in the human being; in fear lies the explanation of everything, original sin as well as original virtue. Out of fear grew also my virtue, which is called: science. ‘Fear of wild beasts has been bred into humans the longest– including fear of the beast they harbour within themselves and fear:– Zarathustra calls it “the inner beast”. ‘This long and ancient fear, finally become refined, spiritual, intellectual– today, it seems to me, it is called: science.’–",
