        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, June 17, 2023 11:19:08 PM",
        "content": "‘Not through enmity does enmity come to an end; enmity comes to an end through friendship’:* this stands at the beginning of Buddha’s teaching— this is not morality speaking, but physiology.—Resentment, born of weakness, harms no one more than the weak person himself— or else, when a rich nature is the premise, it is a superfluous feeling, and to retain mastery over it is practically the proof of richness.",
