        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Monday, June 19, 2023 9:00:29 PM",
        "content": "You pay dearly for being immortal: it means you die numerous times over the course of your life.—There is something I call the rancune* of the great: everything great, be it a work or a deed, once it has been accomplished, immediately turns against whoever did it. By virtue of having done it, he is now weak —he can no longer endure his deed, can no longer face up to it. To have something behind you that you should never have wanted, something that constitutes a nodal point in the destiny of humanity—and from then on to have it on top of you!... It almost crushes you...",
