        "page": 263,
        "location": "4028-4031",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, July 22, 2023 3:44:53 PM",
        "content": "To escape boredom, man works either beyond what his usual needs require, or else he invents play, that is, work that is designed to quiet no need other than that for working in general. He who is tired of play, and has no reason to work because of new needs, is sometimes overcome by the longing for a third state that relates to play as floating does to dancing, as dancing does to walking, a blissful, peaceful state of motion: it is the artist’s and philosopher’s vision of happiness.",
