        "page": 118,
        "location": "1795-1800",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, September 2, 2023 9:18:40 PM",
        "content": "When Hegel writes, “(Being and nothingness) are empty abstractions, and the one is as empty as the other,”7 he forgets that emptiness is emptiness of something.8 Being is empty of all other determination than identity with itself, but non-being is empty of being. In a word, we must recall here against Hegel that being is and that nothingness is not.",
