        "page": 77,
        "location": "1180-1186",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Sunday, September 10, 2023 4:33:12 PM",
        "content": "‘To lure many away from the herd—for that have I come. The people and herd shall be angry with me: Zarathustra wants to be called a robber by the herdsmen. ‘Herdsmen, I say, but they call themselves the good and the righteous. Herdsmen, I say: but they call themselves believers of right belief. ‘Behold the good and the righteous! Whom do they hate the most? The one who breaks their tablets of values,* the breaker, the lawbreaker:—yet that is the creator. ‘Behold the believers of all beliefs! Whom do they hate the most? The one who breaks their tablets of values, the breaker, the lawbreaker:—yet that is the creator.",
