        "page": 97,
        "location": "1473-1476",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Monday, September 11, 2023 3:11:15 PM",
        "content": "I have learned how to walk: since then I let myself run. I have learned how to fly: since then I will not be pushed before moving from my place. Now I am light, now I am flying, now I see myself beneath myself, now a God dances through me. Thus spoke Zarathustra.",
