        "content": "Thus spoke Zarathustra. And he waited for his unhappiness the entire night: but he waited in vain. The night remained clear and still, and happiness itself came closer and closer to him. Toward morning, however, Zarathustra laughed to his heart and said mockingly: ‘Happiness is pursuing me. That comes from my not pursuing women. Happiness, however, is a woman.’",
