        "content": "Knowledge is only then knowledge when it has been acquired by an eﬀort of a man’s own thinking rather than by memory alone. Only when we have forgoten everything that has been taught us do we begin to know truly. I shall not come a hair’s breadth closer to the knowledge of things as long as I look upon them as I have been taught to do. In order to know an object I must approach it as something entirely unknown to me",
