        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Sunday, December 10, 2023 10:17:16 PM",
        "content": "A life entirely free from sorrows and anxieties would prove not only uninteresting but intolerable. For together with the sorrows and the causes of sorrow, all dangers, obstacles and failures would disappear from life, and with them all eﬀort and striving and the excitement of peril and the strain of batle and the triumph of victory. Only the unhindered realization of plans, success without obstacles would remain. We should soon tire of a game of which we know in advance that we must win. Fr. Paulson",
