        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Wednesday, March 6, 2024 1:54:08 PM",
        "content": "To use a simile, it is impossible to know if a house is solid enough to withstand the elements if it has not experienced the buffets of a storm. Wind and rain are external circumstances, the solidity of the house an internal one. Until a storm blows there is no way to prove the solidity of the house. Of course a house will stand if there is no wind or rain, but we can only call a house solid if it will stand up under any gale and any downpour",
