        "page": 27,
        "location": "411-413",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Saturday, March 9, 2024 2:43:33 PM",
        "content": "Prejudice in favor of cold people. People who catch fire rapidly quickly become cold, and are therefore by and large unreliable. Therefore, all those who are always cold, or act that way, benefit from the prejudice that they are especially trustworthy, reliable people: they are being confused with those others who catch fire slowly and burn for a long time.",
