        "page": 474,
        "location": "7262-7265",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Tuesday, March 26, 2024 8:38:25 PM",
        "content": "Relatedly, another aspect of the individualism complex is a preference for choice or control. WEIRD people prefer the things they themselves pick and work harder on tasks they’ve chosen than on identical tasks assigned by an authority. By contrast, less individualistic populations are not particularly inspired by opportunities to make their own choices or to take control.",
