        "page": 475,
        "location": "7273-7278",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Tuesday, March 26, 2024 8:40:01 PM",
        "content": "This evidence suggests not only that medieval Europeans would have been more socially and psychologically susceptible to formal democratic institutions, but that democratic institutions would have actually worked better by inspiring those with a proto-WEIRD psychology to contribute more to the group and follow the rules.",
