        "bookTile": "The WEIRDest People in the World",
        "page": 512,
        "location": "7842-7847",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Wednesday, March 27, 2024 10:58:26 AM",
        "content": "Moreover, unconstrained by the bonds of kinship, learners can potentially select particularly knowledgeable or skilled teachers from this broader network. To see why this is important, consider the difference between learning a crop rotation strategy from the best person in your extended family (a paternal uncle, say) or the best person in your town (the rich farmer with the big house). Your uncle probably had access to the same agricultural know-how as your father, though perhaps he was more attentive than your father or incorporated a few insights of his own. By contrast, the most successful farmer in the community may very well have cultural know-how that your father’s family never acquired, and you may be able to combine insights from him with those from your own family to produce an even better set of routines or practices.",
