        "content": "Nixon looked at him closely. “You see, don’t you? You’ve got to be tough. You can’t break, boy, even when there’s nothing left. You can’t admit, even to yourself, that it is gone. Now some people we both know think that you’ve got to go stand in the middle of the bull ring and cry, ‘mea culpa, mea culpa,’ while the crowd is hissing and booing and spitting on you. But a man doesn’t cry.” Nixon clenched the pipe stem in his teeth. “I don’t cry. You don’t cry.”",
