        "location": "5311-5314",
        "dateOfCreation": "Added on Friday, April 12, 2024 2:07:47 PM",
        "content": "Romans were not, by and large, so unobservant that they would have failed to spot the autocracy lurking behind the fig leaf of ‘the rights of a consul’. The point was that Augustus was cleverly adapting the traditional idioms to serve a new politics, justifying and making comprehensible a new axis of power by systematically reconfiguring an old language.",
