        "content": "Julie recalled. “She had long ago come to understand that my father did not want his family to be involved in his political decisions. He liked to tackle problems by turning them over and over again in his mind until they became digested and resolved. It was a solitary process, and because both my parents were very private people, their relationship was a delicate, private one that did not allow for much second guessing.”",
